The paper deals with the communication of information over a channel in the presence of an adversarial jammer, which is a topic that falls under the information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR) sub-categories. The use of upper bounds and encoding schemes suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the data structures (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Finally, the study of causal adversaries and their decision-making process may also be of interest to the social and information networks (cs.SI) sub-category.
